Class CoalescedHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • CoalescedHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - is the type for the keys
    V - is the type for the values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    KWHashMap<K,V>

    public class CoalescedHashMap<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements KWHashMap<K,V>
    A class that acts like an HashMap. Uses open addressing with quadratic probing also uses coalesced hashing technique.

        A constructor that sets the CAPACITY of the map as the given value. However, if the value is smaller than 7, sets the CAPACITY as 7. Sets the LOAD_TRESHOLD as the given newLoad. It is not suggested to use this, this constructor was done only to test example in the hw pdf.
